  "writeup": "The Buffalo Bills are generating buzz heading into 2026 training camp, with roster battles, contract talks, and position rankings dominating the conversation. New defensive coordinator Jim Leonhard faces what ESPN calls the NFL's toughest task, needing to shore up a defense that struggled on late downs in 2025. On offense, running back James Cook continues to climb NFL rankings while Josh Allen remains a top quarterback by most metrics, and the DJ Moore trade is drawing fresh scrutiny. O'Cyrus Torrence's contract situation adds another layer of intrigue, with both sides expressing mutual desire to get a deal done. Meanwhile, a bizarre subplot emerged from the 2025 season as details surfaced about Sean Payton's failed fake punt call against the Bills — a play his own players refused to run.",
